WEBVTT

00:02.335 --> 00:03.711
- HOT IN CLEVELAND
IS RECORDED IN FRONT

00:03.795 --> 00:05.255
OF A LIVE STUDIO AUDIENCE.

00:05.338 --> 00:10.468
- COUNCILWOMAN, YOU HONOR
US WITH YOUR PRESENCE.

00:10.552 --> 00:11.761
- THIS IS CRAZY.

00:11.845 --> 00:13.763
YOU WON A CITY COUNCIL POST.

00:13.847 --> 00:17.058
WHY IS EVERYONE TREATING YOU
LIKE YOU'RE THE GODFATHER?

00:20.812 --> 00:23.314
- THE COUNCILWOMAN SAYS IT WOULD
BE A SHAME IF SOMETHING WERE

00:23.398 --> 00:28.653
TO HAPPEN TO THOSE LEGS
YOU SO SHAMELESSLY DISPLAY.

00:28.737 --> 00:30.905
- COUNCILWOMAN.

00:30.989 --> 00:35.118
I BRING YOU SPECIAL CANNOLIS
PREPARED BY MY WIFE.

00:35.201 --> 00:40.081
- [as Brando] THIS IS
A NICE THING YOU DO FOR ME.

00:40.165 --> 00:41.916
- COUNCILWOMAN, A REQUEST.

00:42.000 --> 00:45.670
FOOD INSPECTORS, THEY COME HERE,
THEY GIVE ME A "B."

00:45.754 --> 00:47.756
I SAY TO MY STAFF, FOR JUSTICE

00:47.839 --> 00:49.841
WE MUST GO TO
COUNCILWOMAN OSTROVSKY.

00:49.924 --> 00:53.303
- I SEE AN "A" IN YOUR FUTURE.

00:53.386 --> 00:55.597
- THANK YOU, COUNCILWOMAN.

00:55.680 --> 00:57.932
- HOW ARE YOU GOING TO GET THEM
TO CHANGE THE GRADE?

00:58.016 --> 01:02.771
- DON'T ASK ME
ABOUT MY BUSINESS, JOY.

01:02.854 --> 01:04.188
- LOOK, IT'S VICTORIA.

01:04.272 --> 01:06.816
- IS THAT ACADEMY AWARD-WINNER,
VICTORIA CHASE?

01:06.900 --> 01:08.860
- IT IS, IT IS!

01:08.943 --> 01:10.820
- OH, STOP.

01:10.904 --> 01:13.114
THIS IS SO EMBARRASSING.
[giggles]

01:13.198 --> 01:17.285
NOT BAD, BUT YOU FORGOT, "SHE'S
EVEN MORE BEAUTIFUL IN PERSON."

01:17.368 --> 01:18.995
OH, LOOK WHAT I GOT.

01:19.078 --> 01:22.791
IT'S A FAKE OSCAR
I FOUND AT A NOVELTY STORE.

01:22.874 --> 01:24.793
I'M GONNA USE IT
TO FIGURE OUT THE BEST PLACE

01:24.876 --> 01:28.046
TO DISPLAY MY REAL ONE
WHEN IT ARRIVES.

01:28.129 --> 01:30.173
{\an1}- YOU KNOW, I READ THAT WHEN YOU
WON, 80% OF AMERICAN'S THOUGHT

01:30.256 --> 01:33.426
THAT JOHN TRAVOLTA
READ THE WRONG NAME.

01:36.638 --> 01:40.517
- DID I MENTION
IT'S ALSO A WATER PISTOL?

01:40.600 --> 01:41.726
[text alert plays]

01:41.810 --> 01:43.186
- OH, IT'S FROM MITCH.

01:43.269 --> 01:45.021
HE'S GOING OUT OF TOWN
FOR A FEW DAYS.

01:45.104 --> 01:47.857
IT SAYS, "I MISS YOU ALREADY."

01:47.941 --> 01:50.026
- AW. YOU LOOK VERY HAPPY, JOY.
- I AM.

01:50.109 --> 01:52.028
BUT I'M SCARED TO TRUST IT.

01:52.111 --> 01:54.739
IT'S RIDICULOUS, BUT I FEEL LIKE
SOMETHING AWFUL WILL HAPPEN

01:54.823 --> 01:57.075
THE MOMENT I JUST COME OUT
AND SAY I'M HAPPY,

01:57.158 --> 01:59.035
AND I'M IN LOVE WITH MITCH.

01:59.118 --> 02:01.246
[text alert plays]

02:01.329 --> 02:03.706
OH, MY GOD!
SOMETHING AWFUL HAS HAPPENED!

02:03.790 --> 02:05.542
IT'S SIMON.

02:05.625 --> 02:07.418
I HAVEN'T HEARD FROM HIM
IN MONTHS, AND NOW

02:07.502 --> 02:10.547
OUT OF THE BLUE HE WANTS
TO VIDEO CHAT?

02:10.630 --> 02:12.715
OH, I SHOULD GET THIS OVER WITH
RIGHT NOW

02:12.799 --> 02:14.759
AND TELL HIM ABOUT MITCH.

02:14.843 --> 02:17.387
BUT I CAN'T.
- WHY NOT?

02:17.470 --> 02:19.556
- I CAN'T VIDEO CHAT LIKE THIS.

02:19.639 --> 02:21.558
YOU HAVE TO LOOK YOUR SEXIEST
WHEN YOU'RE TELLING A MAN

02:21.641 --> 02:23.351
YOU'RE NEVER GOING TO HAVE SEX
WITH HIM AGAIN.

02:23.434 --> 02:26.145
[overlapping agreement]

02:26.229 --> 02:27.897
- SHALL I CLEAR THE TABLE?

02:27.981 --> 02:29.023
- OH, THANK YOU.

02:29.107 --> 02:30.900
- OH, I'VE SEEN THESE.

02:30.984 --> 02:32.902
IT'S A WATER GUN, RIGHT?

02:32.986 --> 02:34.070
- LEAVE THE GUN.

02:34.153 --> 02:37.156
TAKE THE CANNOLIS.

02:41.327 --> 02:46.082
- THERE, THIS WILL TAKE CARE
OF THE SHADOWS.

02:46.165 --> 02:48.418
YOU'RE ALL SET
FOR YOUR VIDEO CHAT.

02:48.501 --> 02:50.253
JUST REMEMBER, YOUR RIGHT SIDE
IS YOUR BEST,

02:50.336 --> 02:52.422
NEVER SHOW THE LEFT SIDE
OF YOUR FACE.

02:52.505 --> 02:54.048
- WHAT'S WRONG
WITH MY LEFT SIDE?

02:54.132 --> 02:56.301
- NOTHING, IT'S GORGEOUS.

02:56.384 --> 02:58.720
- BUT YOU JUST SAID--
- MELANIE, HELLO!

02:58.803 --> 03:00.471
- SOMETHING TERRIBLE
JUST HAPPENED.

03:00.555 --> 03:02.765
A COP JUST GAVE ME A TICKET.
- WHAT?

03:02.849 --> 03:05.476
WE CAN'T FLIRT OUR WAY
OUT OF TICKETS IN CLEVELAND?

03:05.560 --> 03:07.770
WHY EVEN LIVE HERE?

03:07.854 --> 03:09.439
- NO, IT WAS A FEMALE COP.

03:09.522 --> 03:11.774
AND I GOT CAUGHT UP IN
THE WHOLE ELKA GODFATHER THING.

03:11.858 --> 03:14.110
AND I SAID, IF THE TICKET
WOULD SOMEHOW GO AWAY,

03:14.193 --> 03:16.112
THAT ELKA WOULD GIVE HER
A PROMOTION.

03:16.195 --> 03:16.738
NOW SHE'S GOING
TO INVESTIGATE ELKA.

03:16.821 --> 03:18.781
- WHY WOULD YOU DO THAT?

03:18.865 --> 03:21.075
- I'M WEAK.
I'M FREDO.

03:21.159 --> 03:22.619
- UGH!

03:22.702 --> 03:23.620
[text alert plays]
- OH, MY GOD.

03:23.703 --> 03:25.330
IT'S SIMON.

03:25.413 --> 03:26.372
- OKAY, JUST REMEMBER, YOUR
LEFT SIDE'S YOUR BEST SIDE.

03:26.456 --> 03:27.749
- NO, NO, NO, HER RIGHT SIDE
IS HER BEST SIDE.

03:27.832 --> 03:28.958
HER LEFT SIDE IS CRAP.

03:29.042 --> 03:30.126
- NO, HER RIGHT SIDE IS CRAP.

03:30.209 --> 03:31.753
- GO!

03:31.836 --> 03:33.755
[text alert plays]

03:33.838 --> 03:37.133
- HELLO, SIMON.

03:37.216 --> 03:40.303
HOW ARE YOU?

03:40.386 --> 03:41.804
- [Scottish accent]
JOY, YOU LOOK FANTASTIC.

03:41.888 --> 03:43.181
- DO I?

03:43.264 --> 03:45.475
THIS IS HOW I LOOK
ALL THE TIME NOW.

03:45.558 --> 03:46.935
SINCE YOU LEFT.

03:47.018 --> 03:50.146
- WHY ARE YOUR BREASTS GLOWING?

03:50.229 --> 03:53.149
- THAT HAPPENS ALL THE TIME
NOW TOO.

03:53.232 --> 03:55.818
LOOK, SIMON--

03:55.902 --> 03:57.487
- JOY, I'M SORRY I HAVEN'T BEEN
IN TOUCH LATELY,

03:57.570 --> 03:59.614
BUT I THINK ABOUT YOU
ALL THE TIME.

03:59.697 --> 04:01.824
AND OWEN AND WILBUR.
HOW IS EVERYONE?

04:01.908 --> 04:04.285
- EVERYONE IS DOING GREAT.

04:04.369 --> 04:06.663
BUT THERE'S SOMETHING
I NEED TO TELL YOU.

04:06.746 --> 04:09.999
I'VE MET SOMEONE, AND,
WELL...

04:10.083 --> 04:14.128
I'M IN LOVE.

04:14.212 --> 04:17.339
SIMON?

04:17.423 --> 04:18.716
YOU SEEM TO HAVE FROZEN.

04:18.800 --> 04:20.510
I DON'T KNOW WHAT YOU HEARD.

04:20.593 --> 04:22.011
SIMON.

04:22.095 --> 04:25.640
SIMON!

04:25.723 --> 04:27.350
LOOK CLOSE.

04:27.433 --> 04:28.977
TELL ME WHAT YOU THINK?

04:29.060 --> 04:31.521
IS THIS THE FACE OF A MAN
WHO JUST HEARD ME SAY,

04:31.604 --> 04:34.607
"I'M IN LOVE WITH SOMEONE ELSE"?

04:34.691 --> 04:36.526
- I DON'T KNOW.

04:36.609 --> 04:41.864
BUT THIS IS THE FACE OF SOMEBODY
WHO'S TIRED OF HEARING ABOUT IT.

04:41.948 --> 04:44.909
- JOY, HONEY, WE'VE BEEN
ANALYZING THIS FOR TWO DAYS NOW,

04:44.993 --> 04:47.578
AND, UNTIL YOU REACH HIM, YOU'RE
NOT GOING TO KNOW WHAT HE HEARD.

04:47.662 --> 04:50.039
- I THINK YOU SHOULD
JUST DELETE IT AND MOVE ON.

04:50.123 --> 04:51.666
- I WANT TO, BUT FOR SOME REASON

04:51.749 --> 04:54.043
I CAN'T SEEM TO DELETE
HIS STUPID FACE.

04:54.127 --> 04:56.045
- DO YOU THINK YOU STILL MIGHT
HAVE FEELINGS FOR HIM?

04:56.129 --> 04:57.338
- I DON'T KNOW.

04:57.422 --> 04:58.548
I HOPE NOT.

04:58.631 --> 05:00.508
I'M SO UNSETTLED
ABOUT THE WHOLE THING.

05:00.591 --> 05:02.051
I JUST WISH MITCH
WOULD GET BACK.

05:02.135 --> 05:03.886
- OH, I KNOW HOW YOU FEEL,
HONEY.

05:03.970 --> 05:08.558
I'M WAITING AND HOPING
FOR MY MAN TOO.

05:08.641 --> 05:12.603
- IT'S AN OSCAR, NOT A REAL MAN.

05:12.687 --> 05:14.856
- BUT HE'S MADE OF GOLD,
AND HE HAS NO OPINIONS,

05:14.939 --> 05:16.899
SO IN SOME WAYS HE'S BETTER.

05:16.983 --> 05:19.402
- THAT'S TRUE.

05:19.485 --> 05:21.946
- YOU KNOW, JOY,
WHEN I'M TROUBLED

05:22.030 --> 05:25.575
AND I WANT TO TALK THINGS OUT,
I GO TO CONFESSION.

05:25.658 --> 05:29.203
- THE LAST TIME I WENT
WAS WHEN SIMON GOT ME PREGNANT.

05:29.287 --> 05:33.875
I SUPPOSE GOD
MIGHT ENJOY THE IRONY.

05:33.958 --> 05:35.543
- OH, POOR JOY.

05:35.626 --> 05:40.089
IF ONLY THERE WAS SOME WAY SHE
COULD GET IN TOUCH WITH SIMON.

05:40.173 --> 05:43.051
- I MIGHT BE ABLE
TO HELP WITH THAT.

05:45.887 --> 05:48.431
[upbeat music]

05:48.514 --> 05:50.725
- ♪ BA-BA, BA-BA ♪

05:50.808 --> 05:53.811
♪ BA-BA, BA-BA,
HEY! ♪

05:53.895 --> 05:56.397
{\an8}- OH, MY GOD, SIMON?

05:56.481 --> 05:57.982
{\an8}- WHAT ARE YOU DOING HERE?

05:58.066 --> 05:59.650
{\an8}- BEFORE THE COMPUTER CRASHED,

05:59.734 --> 06:02.111
{\an8}I HEARD ENOUGH TO KNOW
THAT JOY WAS DUMPING ME.

06:02.195 --> 06:04.447
{\an8}I WAS ON THE NEXT FLIGHT
OUT OF THE SUDAN.

06:04.530 --> 06:06.949
{\an8}- HE GOT IN LAST NIGHT.

06:07.033 --> 06:10.953
{\an8}HE STAYED AT MY PLACE.

06:11.037 --> 06:13.790
{\an8}- NOTHING HAPPENED, OBVIOUSLY.

06:13.873 --> 06:16.876
{\an8}- THAT'S OUR STORY.

06:16.959 --> 06:19.629
{\an8}- SIMON, YOU CAN'T
JUST LEAVE JOY AGAIN

06:19.712 --> 06:22.298
{\an8}AND THEN JUST WALTZ BACK INTO
HER LIFE WHENEVER YOU'RE READY.

06:22.381 --> 06:23.966
{\an8}- YEAH, YOU LEFT.

06:24.050 --> 06:25.051
{\an8}SHE FOUND SOMEONE ELSE.
SHE'S HAPPY.

06:25.134 --> 06:26.844
{\an8}BUZZ OFF.
- I MADE A MISTAKE.

06:26.928 --> 06:28.429
{\an8}I SHOULD'VE COME BACK SOONER.

06:28.513 --> 06:30.807
{\an8}I LOVE HER.
I CAN'T LIVE WITHOUT HER.

06:30.890 --> 06:33.142
{\an8}I NEED TO SEE FOR MYSELF
IF THIS MITCH MAKES HER FEEL

06:33.226 --> 06:34.769
{\an8}THE WAY I USED TO MAKE
HER FEEL.

06:34.852 --> 06:35.978
{\an8}- AND HOW ARE YOU GOING
TO DO THAT?

06:36.062 --> 06:37.271
{\an8}JUST UP AND CONFRONT HER?

06:37.355 --> 06:38.815
{\an8}- NO, IF I DID THAT,
SHE'D SEND ME PACKING.

06:38.898 --> 06:40.942
{\an8}I NEED TO FIND A WAY
TO GET CLOSE TO HER

06:41.025 --> 06:42.443
{\an8}WITHOUT HER KNOWING IT'S ME

06:42.527 --> 06:44.654
{\an8}SO I CAN SOFTEN HER UP
A LITTLE BIT FIRST.

06:44.737 --> 06:46.989
{\an8}YOU KNOW, REMIND HER
OF WHAT I USED TO MEAN TO HER.

06:47.073 --> 06:49.784
{\an8}- MM, YOU MEAN TRICK HER
INTO LIKING YOU AGAIN.

06:49.867 --> 06:52.495
{\an8}- LOOK, IF JOY REALLY
LOVES MITCH, THEN THERE'S

06:52.578 --> 06:54.455
{\an8}NOTHING I CAN SAY
THAT'S GONNA CHANGE THAT.

06:54.539 --> 06:56.374
{\an8}AND IF THAT'S THE CASE,
I'LL ADMIT DEFEAT

06:56.457 --> 06:58.334
{\an8}AND HEAD OFF BACK TO KHARTOUM.

06:58.417 --> 07:00.461
- OH, MY GOD,
THIS IS LIKE SOMETHING

07:00.545 --> 07:02.171
OUT OF THOSE GREAT ROM-COMS.

07:02.255 --> 07:04.966
HE FLEW HALFWAY AROUND THE WORLD
JUST TO WIN HER BACK.

07:05.049 --> 07:08.261
WHAT IF SIMON IS HER TRUE LOVE,
AND MITCH IS JUST A REBOUND?

07:08.344 --> 07:10.513
I THINK I'M ON TEAM SIMON.

07:10.596 --> 07:12.348
- I'M STILL ON TEAM MITCH.

07:12.431 --> 07:14.559
I'M SORRY, SIMON,
BUT YOU HAD YOUR CHANCE.

07:14.642 --> 07:16.352
- LET ME TAKE ONE MORE SHOT.

07:16.435 --> 07:18.855
PLEASE.

07:18.938 --> 07:20.815
- ALL RIGHT.

07:20.898 --> 07:23.151
I NEED SOMETHING TO FILL THE
TIME UNTIL MY OSCAR GETS HERE.

07:23.234 --> 07:27.029
SO IS IT BIG NEWS
IN SUDAN THAT I WON?

07:27.113 --> 07:31.200
- PEOPLE ARE FIGHTING
AND DYING THERE.

07:31.284 --> 07:34.704
- IS THAT A YES OR A NO?

07:34.787 --> 07:36.706
- I HAVE AN IDEA.

07:36.789 --> 07:38.499
IF YOU NEED A DISGUISE,

07:38.583 --> 07:40.918
MAYBE YOU SHOULD BE
A SCOTTISH NANNY,

07:41.002 --> 07:45.339
LIKE MRS. DOUBTFIRE.

07:45.423 --> 07:47.341
- WHAT A GREAT MOVIE THAT WAS.

07:47.425 --> 07:51.596
- MY FAVORITE PART
WAS WHEN THE POTS BOILED OVER.

07:51.679 --> 07:57.226
- THERE'S NOTHING FUNNIER
THAN BOOBS ON FIRE.

07:57.310 --> 07:58.686
- SO IT'S SETTLED.

07:58.769 --> 08:01.105
- NO, IT'S NOT SETTLED!

08:01.189 --> 08:03.399
I'M NOT BEING MRS. DOUBTFIRE.

08:03.482 --> 08:05.902
I'LL COME UP
WITH SOMETHING BETTER.

08:05.985 --> 08:06.903
[text alert plays]

08:06.986 --> 08:08.112
- [gasps]

08:08.196 --> 08:09.906
COUNCILWOMAN.

08:09.989 --> 08:11.616
SOMEBODY TRIED
TO BRIBE A POLICE OFFICER

08:11.699 --> 08:13.910
USING YOUR NAME.

08:13.993 --> 08:16.245
WE HAVE A RAT IN OUR MIDST.

08:16.329 --> 08:21.083
- THIS DOES NOT PLEASE ME.

08:21.167 --> 08:23.544
- DID THEY MENTION A NAME?

08:23.628 --> 08:25.713
- NO, BUT WE'LL FIND OUT
WHO IT IS.

08:25.796 --> 08:30.009
AND WHEN WE DO,
WE GO TO THE MATTRESSES.

08:34.138 --> 08:35.890
- WHAT?

08:35.972 --> 08:38.808
- WE ALWAYS THINK BETTER
AFTER A NICE NAP.

08:46.150 --> 08:47.652
- HELLO, FATHER.

08:47.735 --> 08:51.614
IT'S BEEN 30 YEARS OR SO
SINCE MY LAST CONFESSION.

08:51.697 --> 08:55.785
SO, IF I CONFESS MY SINS,
IT WOULD TAKE WAY TOO LONG.

08:55.868 --> 08:58.955
I'D ACTUALLY JUST LIKE TO TALK
ABOUT A GUY, IF THAT'S OKAY.

08:59.038 --> 09:02.208
- [resonant voice]
TELL ME EVERYTHING, MY CHILD.

09:08.881 --> 09:09.966
- HIS NAME IS SIMON.

09:10.049 --> 09:12.593
- SIMON.
THERE'S A GOOD STRONG NAME.

09:12.677 --> 09:16.430
I'M PRETTY SURE HE WAS ONE
OF THE APOSTLES.

09:18.766 --> 09:20.559
- PRETTY SURE?

09:20.643 --> 09:23.020
- [clears throat]
TELL ME ABOUT HIM.

09:23.104 --> 09:24.689
- HE WAS MY FIRST LOVE.

09:24.772 --> 09:27.650
WE HAD A CHILD TOGETHER
THAT I GAVE UP FOR ADOPTION,

09:27.733 --> 09:30.778
AND JUST RECENTLY HE'S COME BACK
INTO MY LIFE AGAIN.

09:30.861 --> 09:32.989
- SOUNDS LIKE YOU'RE
STILL IN LOVE WITH HIM.

09:33.072 --> 09:35.324
- NO. I MEAN, I WAS.

09:35.408 --> 09:36.492
I DON'T KNOW.

09:36.575 --> 09:39.120
I FOUND SOMEONE ELSE,
AND I'M HAPPY.

09:39.203 --> 09:40.663
HIS NAME IS MITCH AND--

09:40.746 --> 09:43.708
- I'VE NEVER CARED
FOR THAT NAME.

09:43.791 --> 09:48.170
THERE'S THE STORY IN THE BIBLE
OF A MITCH

09:48.254 --> 09:49.672
WHO BROKE WOMEN'S HEARTS

09:49.755 --> 09:55.011
AND, UM, FORNICATED WITH GOATS.

09:55.094 --> 09:57.013
- REALLY?
- MM.

09:57.096 --> 09:59.098
- WELL, MY MITCH
IS NOT LIKE THAT.

09:59.181 --> 10:01.976
WHEN I FIRST SAW HIM, I HAD
THE FEELING THAT HE WAS THE MAN

10:02.059 --> 10:04.353
I WAS GOING TO MARRY.

10:04.437 --> 10:06.564
I THINK HE'S MY SOUL MATE.

10:06.647 --> 10:08.899
- DID YOU EVER THINK SIMON
WAS YOUR SOUL MATE?

10:08.983 --> 10:10.359
- I DID.

10:10.443 --> 10:13.112
AND I FELT HAPPY AND FULFILLED
WHEN HE CAME BACK.

10:13.195 --> 10:14.864
THEN HE LEFT.

10:14.947 --> 10:15.906
HE ALWAYS LEAVES.

10:15.990 --> 10:17.366
THAT'S WHAT HE DOES.

10:17.450 --> 10:20.202
- DID HE LEAVE
FOR SOME VILE REASON?

10:20.286 --> 10:22.038
- NO.

10:22.121 --> 10:24.582
HE STOPPED BEING A PAPARAZZI
FOR ME AND LEFT TO DO SOMETHING

10:24.665 --> 10:27.710
NOBLE WITH HIS LIFE SO HIS
GRANDSON WOULD BE PROUD OF HIM.

10:27.793 --> 10:31.881
- SO YOUR ORIGINAL SOUL MATE
IS A HERO.

10:33.883 --> 10:35.343
- MAYBE.

10:35.426 --> 10:37.219
- SOUNDS LIKE YOU MISS HIM.

10:37.303 --> 10:39.722
I BET HE MISSES YOU TOO.

10:39.805 --> 10:42.516
- I FEEL CONFUSED.

10:42.600 --> 10:47.021
- WELL, AS THE CHURCH SAYS,
IT'S GOOD TO DOUBT.

10:51.400 --> 10:54.195
- YOU'RE A VERY UNUSUAL PRIEST.

10:54.278 --> 10:59.325
- WELL, YOU KNOW,
NEW POPE, NEW RULES.

11:01.702 --> 11:03.704
- ELKA'S GOING TO FIND OUT
I'M THE RAT.

11:03.788 --> 11:04.705
- WELL, SO WHAT?

11:04.789 --> 11:06.207
SHE'S NOT REALLY THE GODFATHER.

11:06.290 --> 11:07.833
SHE'S NOT GOING TO DO
ANYTHING TO YOU.

11:07.917 --> 11:09.460
- BUT SHE'S GOING TO BE
SO DISAPPOINTED IN ME.

11:09.543 --> 11:11.128
I MEAN, I'M THE GOOD ONE.

11:11.212 --> 11:12.296
I'M THE SWEET ONE.

11:12.380 --> 11:16.050
YOU HAVE NO IDEA
WHAT THAT'S LIKE.

11:16.133 --> 11:19.553
- NO, I DON'T,
BUT IT SOUNDS DULL.

11:19.637 --> 11:20.971
OH, LOOK, THERE'S JOY.

11:21.055 --> 11:22.973
SO HOW DID THINGS GO
WITH THE PRIEST?

11:23.057 --> 11:23.933
- TERRIBLE.

11:24.016 --> 11:25.893
I WENT THERE HOPING TO GET SIMON
OFF MY MIND.

11:25.976 --> 11:27.603
NOW HE'S ALL I CAN THINK ABOUT.

11:27.686 --> 11:29.939
I ALMOST THOUGHT
I SMELLED HIS COLOGNE.

11:30.022 --> 11:31.482
I'M SORRY, GUYS.

11:31.565 --> 11:32.650
I'M NOT GOOD COMPANY RIGHT NOW.

11:32.733 --> 11:35.778
I'M JUST GONNA TAKE MY WINE
TO GO.

11:48.833 --> 11:52.253
- WOW, JOY REALLY SEEMS
TORN ABOUT SIMON.

11:52.336 --> 11:53.629
- I KNOW.

11:53.712 --> 11:54.839
ISN'T IT GREAT?

11:54.922 --> 11:57.174
THE SEED OF DOUBT
HAS BEEN PLANTED.

11:57.258 --> 11:59.635
SHE'S WEAK AND VULNERABLE
AND DRINKING HEAVILY.

11:59.718 --> 12:03.431
SHE'S THE WOMAN
I FELL IN LOVE WITH.

12:03.514 --> 12:06.183
- I'M NOT SO SURE THIS
IS IN JOY'S BEST INTEREST.

12:06.267 --> 12:08.853
I'M SORRY, SIMON,
BUT I'M ON TEAM MITCH NOW.

12:08.936 --> 12:10.980
- WELL, I'M SWITCHING
